title: What We Learned From Week 9 in the N.F.L.
description: The Jets’ defense had a counter for the Bills’ top-rated offense, Tom Brady stirred up some old magic, and Joe Burrow got a lift from Bengals not named Ja’Marr Chase.
dc:creator: Derrik Klassen
media:credit: Robert Deutsch/USA Today Sports, via Reuters
media:description: Bills quarterback Josh Allen, middle, was sacked five times and threw two interceptions in a loss to the Jets on Sunday.
